</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCE0253FFB6454CFF0FFA00FB6181BB" blockId="3.[174,1233,228,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="474">
<keyLead id="3080A166FFB6454CFF0FFA00FB6181BB" pageId="3" pageNumber="474">
— Basal segments of hind tarsus dark. 1st segment of hind tarsus with three strong and a few weaker bristles. 1st segment of mid tarsus with one strong bristle. Basal surstyli well developed, asymmetric, on left side of triangular shape and on right side of oval shape. Face pale yellow. Cercus ca. 2× as long as wide. … 
